</taxonomicNameLabel>
: A, male holotype (dorsal habitus); B, female paratype (dorsal habitus); C, female paratype, living specimen. 
<taxonomicName box="[518,772,1591,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Chromatophotina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cofan" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[518,772,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Chromatophotina cofan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[779,839,1590,1614]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[779,839,1590,1614]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: D, female holotype (dorsal habitus).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1657,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,411,1657,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Female 
<typeStatus box="[299,411,1657,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">paratype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Color mostly green (
<figureCitation box="[675,744,1658,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[170,1436,215,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1441,197,1521]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chromatophotina awajun n. sp.: A, male holotype (dorsal habitus); B, female paratype (dorsal habitus); C, female paratype, living specimen. Chromatophotina cofan n. sp.: D, female holotype (dorsal habitus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294123/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[732,744,1658,1684]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C); in live specimen, white lateral stripes on pronotum and costal area of wings (
<figureCitation box="[449,516,1695,1721]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[170,1436,215,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1441,197,1521]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chromatophotina awajun n. sp.: A, male holotype (dorsal habitus); B, female paratype (dorsal habitus); C, female paratype, living specimen. Chromatophotina cofan n. sp.: D, female holotype (dorsal habitus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294123/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[504,516,1695,1721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Measurements (in mm): body length, 
<number box="[1005,1060,1695,1721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="31.5">31.5</number>
; pronotum, 
<number box="[1200,1254,1695,1721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="12.1">12.1</number>
; fore coxa, 7.0; fore femur, 
<number box="[289,329,1732,1758]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="9.3">9.3</number>
; fore tibia, 5.0; mesothoracic wing, 15.0 (length), 
<number box="[917,954,1732,1758]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="5.5">5.5</number>
(width); metathoracic wing, 
<number box="[1294,1349,1732,1758]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="12.2">12.2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1657,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Head pentagonal in shape (
<figureCitation box="[521,591,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,257,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[166,1418,511,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,495,1811]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chromatophotina awajun (female paratype): A, head (frontal view); B, pronotum (dorsal view); C, fore femur and tibia (external view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294125/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[577,591,1770,1796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A), juxtaocular tubercles weakly developed, clearly more elevated than the imaginary line connecting the top of the compound eyes; vertex slightly concave, as elevated as the juxtaocular tubercles; frontal shield transversal, width approximately 
<number box="[979,1016,1844,1870]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="4.6">4.6</number>
times greater than length. Antenna filiform, basal half yellowish-green, progressively turning dark brown towards the tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1657,2020]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,402]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Pronotum slender (
<figureCitation box="[437,545,1919,1945]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,257,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[166,1418,511,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,495,1811]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chromatophotina awajun (female paratype): A, head (frontal view); B, pronotum (dorsal view); C, fore femur and tibia (external view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294125/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
Figure 
<number box="[530,545,1919,1945]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B); lateral edges bearing small denticles. Fore coxae with all margins exhibiting small denticles, all surfaces in general with small, scattered tubercles. Dorsal edge of fore femora almost straight, crenulated. Spination formula: F= 
<number box="[737,801,1994,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16-17</number>
IS/ 
<number box="[836,850,1994,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="6.0">6</number>
ES/ 
<number box="[895,908,1994,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
DS and T= 
<number box="[1040,1068,1994,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="18.0">18</number>
IS/ 
<number box="[1104,1177,1994,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" value="18.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="18.0">18–19</number>
ES. Femora and tibiae with straight dorsal edges (
<figureCitation box="[465,534,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,257,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[166,1418,511,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,495,1811]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chromatophotina awajun (female paratype): A, head (frontal view); B, pronotum (dorsal view); C, fore femur and tibia (external view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294125/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[520,534,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C) and all spines with black tips. Small denticles scattered among and around the external spines. Sternum glabrous. Mesothoracic wings opaque, green, except for costal area, which is white and covered with white, dusty matter. Metathoracic wings short; costal area greenish-white. Discal area yellow, becoming bright orange towards the anal area. When folded, wings reaching the second half of sixth abdominal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,402]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">Supra-anal plate trapezoidal slightly notched distally. Cerci long, slightly flattened, longer than supra-anal plate, mostly green but each segment with a purplish-black coloration ventromedially.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
